And the Winner Is...

See Who Took Home the SPCEL03 Industrial Edge Computer

We Have a Winner!

Thank you to everyone who entered our InfoComm 2025 in-show giveaway and visited us at Booth 4874. We had an incredible response from attendees across industries, and we appreciate your enthusiasm, interest, and conversations throughout the event. Your participation made this year’s show one of our most engaging yet.

 

We’re excited to announce that Ian Wood-Ward Smith has been selected as the winner of our raffle. Ian will receive a fully configured SPCEL03 Industrial Edge Computer system, including Windows IOT. Purpose-built for rugged environments and edge performance.

SPCEL03 | Compact and Durable

Key Features:

  • Intel® Atom x6413E Elkhart Lake processor

  • Wide Temp Computer -20c to 60c

  • Up to 32GB DDR4-3200 RAM

  • Smallest PICO-ITX motherboard

  • 3-pin terminal block (9v-24v), GPIO

 

Ideal for edge computing, automation, digital signage, data logging, and video surveillance

We appreciate everyone who took the time to engage with our team and explore our compact, high-performance solutions. Stay tuned for future product announcements and giveaways, and we look forward to seeing you at InfoComm 2026 in Las Vegas. Stay connected with Shuttle for the latest updates.
